                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d249">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">722.2315/1391: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Peru</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Norweb</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="9" xml:id="d249fn1">On the same date a telegram was sent to
                        the Minister in Ecuador as No. 16, giving the substance of this telegram and
                        of telegram No. 11, January 14, 1 p.m., from the Ambassador in Peru, <hi
                            rend="italic">supra.</hi>
                    </note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-01-30T15:00:00-05:00"
                            >January 30, 1941—3 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>18. Your 11, January 14, 1 p.m. The following telegram was received on January 24
                    from the American Chargé d’Affaires at Rio de Janeiro: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“Aranha today requested me to inform you that after giving adequate
                            consideration to your message he applauds the initiative put forward by
                            the Peruvian Minister for Foreign Affairs and will support the idea. He
                            said that he would undertake to recommend this plan to both Governments
                            and would at once speak to the Peruvian Ambassador and the Ecuadoran
                            Minister here in that sense.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
